data.content:
Created both files. Here's how the component works:

**`SortableList.razor`** — Iterates the internal `_items` list, renders each item via `ItemTemplate`, and adds Move Up / Move Down buttons (disabled at boundaries).

**`SortableList.razor.cs`** — Key design points:
- **Generic** (`TItem`) — works with any item type.
- **Internal copy** — `SetParametersAsync` copies the incoming list into `_items` only when the reference changes, so the parent's list is never mutated.
- **`OnOrderChanged`** — fires after each swap, passing back a `IReadOnlyList<TItem>` snapshot so the parent can update its own state.

Usage matches your example exactly:

```razor
<SortableList Items="@tasks" OnOrderChanged="HandleReorder">
    <ItemTemplate>
        <span>@context.Title</span>
    </ItemTemplate>
</SortableList>

@code {
    List<TaskItem> tasks = new() { /* ... */ };

    void HandleReorder(IReadOnlyList<TaskItem> updated)
    {
        tasks = updated.ToList();
    }
}
```
